{"title_page": "Kwabena Agyapong", "text_new": "{{short description|Ghanaian politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n\n'''Kwabena Agyei Agyapong''' (born 6 March 1962) is [[Ghanaian]] Civil Engineer, [[Politician]] and Sports Journalist.  \n\n==Early life==\nAgyapong was born on 6 March 1962, in [[Kumasi]], Capital of the [[Ashanti Region]] of [[Ghana]]. He was the son of Justice Kwadwo Agyei Agyepong, one of three prominent Ghanaian judges who was abducted and murdered during the early years of Ghana's [[Provisional National Defence Council]]. (PNDC).<ref>[[Joachim Amartey Quaye]]</ref> He had his secondary school education at [[Mfantsipim School]].\n\n==Life in Politics==\nAgyapong belongs to the [[New Patriotic Party]] of Ghana. He became active in Ghanaian politics when Ghana reentered constitutional rule after over a decade of Military rule. He played roles in the campaigns of NPP Presidential Candidates [[Albert Adu Boahen]] in 1992, [[John Kufuor]] in 1996. He also played a role in [[Nana Akufo-Addo]]'s campaign to win the presidential nomination in 1998 but subsequently played a role in the overall party effort during the 2000 General election which was won by John Kufuor. He was involved in this again in the year 2004.\n\nHe served as the Press Secretary to the [[President of Ghana]] [[John Kufuor]] from 2001 to 2006. Kwabena Agyapong was one of 17 aspirants who contested for the party's nomination to replace John Agyekum Kuffuor as presidential candidate for the 2008 Ghanaian General Election,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/features/artikel.php?ID=130188|title=17 questions for 17 presidential aspirants|website=www.ghanaweb.com|language=en|access-date=2017-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/200710091054.html|title=Ghana: Kwabena Agyei Agyapong Files Nomination|last=Amankwah|first=Ama Achiaa|date=2007-10-09|work=Public Agenda (Accra)|access-date=2017-12-15}}</ref>\nIn 2014, Kwabena Agyapong stood for the position of General Secretary for the Party and won. However, he and the party's chairman, [[Paul Afoko]] faced a lot of resistance in trying to do their duties.<ref>http://citifmonline.com/2014/04/13/provisional-results-afoko-kwabena-agyepong-sammy-awuku-in-jake-sir-john-out/</ref>\n\nKwabena Agyapong and one Vice Chairman of the party, Sammy Crabbe were suspended by the party from their positions after receipt of petitions from some members of the party. This was after the Chairman of the party had also been suspended earlier on through a similar process. Afoko and Crabbe had hinted of mounting legal challenges against their suspensions which they claim were done illegally.,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/politics/2015/December-10th/npp-suspends-kwabena-agyepong-crabbe-indefinitely.php|title=NPP suspends Kwabena Agyepong, Crabbe indefinitely - MyJoyOnline.com|website=www.myjoyonline.com|access-date=2017-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/politics/2016/January-20th/sammy-crabbe-vows-to-expose-npp-coup-makers-in-court.php|title=Sammy Crabbe vows to expose NPP 'coup makers' in court - MyJoyOnline.com|website=www.myjoyonline.com|access-date=2017-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://pulse.com.gh/politics/npp-infighting-afoko-heads-to-court-over-suspension-id4353988.html|title=NPP Infighting: Afoko heads to court over suspension|last=Taylor|first=Mildred Europa|access-date=2017-12-15|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Controversy==\nAfter having won their elections together with others, Kwabena Agyapong and the Party's Chairmanship, [[Paul Afoko]] faced a lot of resistance. Things came to a head when a party meeting was called when Afoko was out of Ghana and Agyapong was in [[Kumasi]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://graphic.com.gh/news/politics/42793-steering-c-ttee-meeting-without-afoko-agyepong-disturbing-dr-nyaho-tamakloe.html|title=Steering C\u2019ttee meeting without  Afoko, Agyepong disturbing \u2014 Dr Nyaho-Tamakloe - Graphic Online|last=Asmah|first=Kobby|work=Graphic Online|access-date=2017-12-15|language=en-GB}}</ref> Later, the two went around the country to meet party officials but were chased away by some party supporters and had to be saved by the police.<ref>\n{{Cite web |url=http://www.starrfmonline.com/1.3739031 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-05-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150522111641/http://www.starrfmonline.com/1.3739031 |archive-date=2015-05-22 |url-status=dead }}\n</ref> The Party Chairman of the region, Adam Mahama justified the attack on the two but later apologized.<ref>\n{{Cite web|url=http://ghanacrusader.com/upper-east-npp-chairman-apologizes-to-afoko-agyapong/|title=New Home|website=GhanaCrusader.com - Latest News in Ghana and Beyond|language=en-US|access-date=2017-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160403165653/http://www.ghanacrusader.com/upper-east-npp-chairman-apologizes-to-afoko-agyapong/|archive-date=2016-04-03|url-status=dead}}\n</ref> In the night of 20 May 2015, Adam Mahama was attacked by assailants who poured acid on him. He died in the hospital on 21 May 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/politics/2015/May-21st/upper-east-assailants-pour-acid-on-npp-chairman.php|title=Photos: Upper East NPP chairman dies after acid attack - MyJoyOnline.com|website=www.myjoyonline.com|access-date=2017-12-15}}</ref>\nPrior to his death, Adam Mahama was alleged to have mentioned that Paul Afoko's brother, Gregory was one of those who assaulted and poured acid on him. The Police subsequently arrested Gregory, investigated and presented him before the courts.<ref>http://citifmonline.com/2015/05/26/afokos-brother-in-court-photos/</ref>\nCalls for Paul Afoko and Agyapong to be pushed out of the party, which started before the murder however continued to grow.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/619828/1/mr-afoko-and-kwabena-agyepong.html|title=Mr. Afoko And Kwabena Agyepong Must Resign!!|last=(STUNNAD)|first=STUDENTS NETWORK FOR NANA ADDO|work=Modern Ghana|access-date=2017-12-15|language=en-gb}}</ref>\n\nAfter several methods to get them out of the party failed, petitions were made by some members of the party to the disciplinary committee of the party, which recommended Afoko's suspension. Afoko was suspended though he disputed the legality of the suspension. Later on the same method was used to suspend Kwabena Agyapong as well as one Vice Chairman of the party, Sammy Crabbe.\n\n==Personal life==\nHe attended the [[Mfantsipim School]] in Cape Coast and obtained a BSc Degree in [[Civil Engineering]] from the [[Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology]] in Kumasi. Kwabena Ayepong for a long period of time hosted sports Programmes on Ghana's State Television Station owned by the [[Ghana Broadcasting Corporation]].\n\nAgyapong worked for a long time with the Ghana Highway Authority. He also owns a civil engineering firm, Constro Consult Limited.\nKwabena Agyapong is Married to Lawrencia Agyapong and has three children.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/151062/1/profile-kwabena-agyei-agyapong.html|title=Profile: Kwabena Agyei Agyapong|work=Modern Ghana|access-date=2017-12-15|language=en-gb}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Agyapong, Kwabena}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Patriotic Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian democracy activists]]\n[[Category:Mfantsipim School alumni]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian engineers]]\n[[Category:Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Kumasi]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ghanaian politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n\n'''Kwabena Agyei Agyapong''' (born 6 March 1962) is [[Ghanaian]] Civil Engineer, [[Politician]] and Sports Journalist. He is suspended general secretary of the New Patriotic Party.\n\n==Early life==\nAgyapong was born on 6 March 1962, in [[Kumasi]], Capital of the [[Ashanti Region]] of [[Ghana]]. He was the son of Justice Kwadwo Agyei Agyepong, one of three prominent Ghanaian judges who was abducted and murdered during the early years of Ghana's [[Provisional National Defence Council]]. (PNDC).<ref>[[Joachim Amartey Quaye]]</ref> He had his secondary school education at [[Mfantsipim School]].\n\n==Life in Politics==\nAgyapong belongs to the [[New Patriotic Party]] of Ghana. He became active in Ghanaian politics when Ghana reentered constitutional rule after over a decade of Military rule. He played roles in the campaigns of NPP Presidential Candidates [[Albert Adu Boahen]] in 1992, [[John Kufuor]] in 1996. He also played a role in [[Nana Akufo-Addo]]'s campaign to win the presidential nomination in 1998 but subsequently played a role in the overall party effort during the 2000 General election which was won by John Kufuor. He was involved in this again in the year 2004.\n\nHe served as the Press Secretary to the [[President of Ghana]] [[John Kufuor]] from 2001 to 2006. Kwabena Agyapong was one of 17 aspirants who contested for the party's nomination to replace John Agyekum Kuffuor as presidential candidate for the 2008 Ghanaian General Election,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/features/artikel.php?ID=130188|title=17 questions for 17 presidential aspirants|website=www.ghanaweb.com|language=en|access-date=2017-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/200710091054.html|title=Ghana: Kwabena Agyei Agyapong Files Nomination|last=Amankwah|first=Ama Achiaa|date=2007-10-09|work=Public Agenda (Accra)|access-date=2017-12-15}}</ref>\nIn 2014, Kwabena Agyapong stood for the position of General Secretary for the Party and won. However, he and the party's chairman, [[Paul Afoko]] faced a lot of resistance in trying to do their duties.<ref>http://citifmonline.com/2014/04/13/provisional-results-afoko-kwabena-agyepong-sammy-awuku-in-jake-sir-john-out/</ref>\n\nKwabena Agyapong and one Vice Chairman of the party, Sammy Crabbe were suspended by the party from their positions after receipt of petitions from some members of the party. This was after the Chairman of the party had also been suspended earlier on through a similar process. Afoko and Crabbe had hinted of mounting legal challenges against their suspensions which they claim were done illegally.,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/politics/2015/December-10th/npp-suspends-kwabena-agyepong-crabbe-indefinitely.php|title=NPP suspends Kwabena Agyepong, Crabbe indefinitely - MyJoyOnline.com|website=www.myjoyonline.com|access-date=2017-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/politics/2016/January-20th/sammy-crabbe-vows-to-expose-npp-coup-makers-in-court.php|title=Sammy Crabbe vows to expose NPP 'coup makers' in court - MyJoyOnline.com|website=www.myjoyonline.com|access-date=2017-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://pulse.com.gh/politics/npp-infighting-afoko-heads-to-court-over-suspension-id4353988.html|title=NPP Infighting: Afoko heads to court over suspension|last=Taylor|first=Mildred Europa|access-date=2017-12-15|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Controversy==\nAfter having won their elections together with others, Kwabena Agyapong and the Party's Chairmanship, [[Paul Afoko]] faced a lot of resistance. Things came to a head when a party meeting was called when Afoko was out of Ghana and Agyapong was in [[Kumasi]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://graphic.com.gh/news/politics/42793-steering-c-ttee-meeting-without-afoko-agyepong-disturbing-dr-nyaho-tamakloe.html|title=Steering C\u2019ttee meeting without  Afoko, Agyepong disturbing \u2014 Dr Nyaho-Tamakloe - Graphic Online|last=Asmah|first=Kobby|work=Graphic Online|access-date=2017-12-15|language=en-GB}}</ref> Later, the two went around the country to meet party officials but were chased away by some party supporters and had to be saved by the police.<ref>\n{{Cite web |url=http://www.starrfmonline.com/1.3739031 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-05-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150522111641/http://www.starrfmonline.com/1.3739031 |archive-date=2015-05-22 |url-status=dead }}\n</ref> The Party Chairman of the region, Adam Mahama justified the attack on the two but later apologized.<ref>\n{{Cite web|url=http://ghanacrusader.com/upper-east-npp-chairman-apologizes-to-afoko-agyapong/|title=New Home|website=GhanaCrusader.com - Latest News in Ghana and Beyond|language=en-US|access-date=2017-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160403165653/http://www.ghanacrusader.com/upper-east-npp-chairman-apologizes-to-afoko-agyapong/|archive-date=2016-04-03|url-status=dead}}\n</ref> In the night of 20 May 2015, Adam Mahama was attacked by assailants who poured acid on him. He died in the hospital on 21 May 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/politics/2015/May-21st/upper-east-assailants-pour-acid-on-npp-chairman.php|title=Photos: Upper East NPP chairman dies after acid attack - MyJoyOnline.com|website=www.myjoyonline.com|access-date=2017-12-15}}</ref>\nPrior to his death, Adam Mahama was alleged to have mentioned that Paul Afoko's brother, Gregory was one of those who assaulted and poured acid on him. The Police subsequently arrested Gregory, investigated and presented him before the courts.<ref>http://citifmonline.com/2015/05/26/afokos-brother-in-court-photos/</ref>\nCalls for Paul Afoko and Agyapong to be pushed out of the party, which started before the murder however continued to grow.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/619828/1/mr-afoko-and-kwabena-agyepong.html|title=Mr. Afoko And Kwabena Agyepong Must Resign!!|last=(STUNNAD)|first=STUDENTS NETWORK FOR NANA ADDO|work=Modern Ghana|access-date=2017-12-15|language=en-gb}}</ref>\n\nAfter several methods to get them out of the party failed, petitions were made by some members of the party to the disciplinary committee of the party, which recommended Afoko's suspension. Afoko was suspended though he disputed the legality of the suspension. Later on the same method was used to suspend Kwabena Agyapong as well as one Vice Chairman of the party, Sammy Crabbe.\n\n==Personal life==\nHe attended the [[Mfantsipim School]] in Cape Coast and obtained a BSc Degree in [[Civil Engineering]] from the [[Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology]] in Kumasi. Kwabena Ayepong for a long period of time hosted sports Programmes on Ghana's State Television Station owned by the [[Ghana Broadcasting Corporation]].\n\nAgyapong worked for a long time with the Ghana Highway Authority. He also owns a civil engineering firm, Constro Consult Limited.\nKwabena Agyapong is Married to Lawrencia Agyapong and has three children.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.modernghana.com/news/151062/1/profile-kwabena-agyei-agyapong.html|title=Profile: Kwabena Agyei Agyapong|work=Modern Ghana|access-date=2017-12-15|language=en-gb}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Agyapong, Kwabena}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Patriotic Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian democracy activists]]\n[[Category:Mfantsipim School alumni]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian engineers]]\n[[Category:Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Kumasi]]\n", "name_user": "Kwadkwk", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kwabena_Agyapong"}
